   198→  "text": "gRPC error status codes are propagated and translated differently across the three repositories:

## etcd-io/etcd
The etcd repository implements comprehensive gRPC error status code creation in `api/v3rpc/rpctypes/error.go`. This file defines pre-constructed error variables using `status.Error()` with specific gRPC codes: `codes.NotFound` (ErrGRPCLeaseNotFound, ErrGRPCMemberNotFound), `codes.FailedPrecondition` (ErrGRPCLeaseExist, ErrGRPCMemberExist), `codes.InvalidArgument` (ErrGRPCEmptyKey, ErrGRPCInvalidSortOption), `codes.PermissionDenied` (ErrGRPCPermissionDenied), `codes.ResourceExhausted` (ErrGRPCRequestTooManyRequests, ErrGRPCNoSpace), `codes.Unavailable` (ErrGRPCTimeout, ErrGRPCNoLeader), and others. The Error() function converts errors between gRPC status format and EtcdError struct with Code() method. For HTTP translation, etcd uses gRPC gateway (`api/etcdserverpb/gw/rpc.pb.gw.go`) which automatically translates gRPC codes to HTTP status codes. The `server/etcdserver/api/v3rpc/interceptor.go` implements unary and stream interceptors that check for server capabilities and membership status, returning pre-defined errors from rpctypes when validation fails.

## kubernetes/kubernetes
Kubernetes uses multiple layers for error handling. The `pkg/kubelet/apis/grpc/ratelimit.go` defines ErrorLimitExceeded using `status.Error(codes.ResourceExhausted, ...)` and implements LimiterUnaryServerInterceptor to enforce rate limiting. For HTTP response translation, the gRPC gateway vendor library (`vendor/github.com/grpc-ecosystem/grpc-gateway/v2/runtime/errors.go`) provides HTTPStatusFromCode() function that maps gRPC codes to HTTP status: `codes.NotFound` → 404, `codes.InvalidArgument` → 400, `codes.PermissionDenied` → 403, `codes.Internal` → 500, etc. The DefaultHTTPErrorHandler uses status.Convert() to extract the gRPC code and map it. For API server error handling, `staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/endpoints/handlers/responsewriters/writers.go` implements ErrorNegotiated() which calls ErrorToAPIStatus() in `status.go`. ErrorToAPIStatus() converts any statusError interface (which StatusError in `staging/src/k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/api/errors/errors.go` implements) to metav1.Status with HTTP codes. The RequestScope.err() method in `rest.go` delegates to ErrorNegotiated for serialization.

## grafana/grafana
Grafana's authorization service (`pkg/services/authz/rbac/service.go`) creates gRPC status errors directly inline using `status.Error()` and `status.Errorf()` with codes: `codes.Internal`, `codes.InvalidArgument`, `codes.PermissionDenied`, `codes.NotFound`. Methods like Check() and BatchCheck() return these errors which propagate through the gRPC framework. The gRPC server infrastructure in `pkg/services/grpcserver/service.go` chains unary and stream interceptors including LoggingUnaryInterceptor and TracingStreamInterceptor from `pkg/services/grpcserver/interceptors/logging.go`. For Zanzana/OpenFGA authorization server (`pkg/services/authz/zanzana/server/openfga_server.go`), errors are converted using `status.Convert()` and `status.FromError()` to work with the gRPC status package, maintaining compatibility with HTTP error translation via the gRPC gateway mechanism.

## Common Pattern
All three repositories follow the pattern: gRPC handler code creates `status.Error(code, message)` → gRPC server propagates to client → gRPC gateway or middleware translates gRPC codes to HTTP status codes using standardized mappings (NotFound→404, InvalidArgument→400, Internal→500, etc.). etcd uses explicit error definitions, Kubernetes uses multiple abstraction layers with StatusError interface, and Grafana creates errors inline during validation."
